Q3.Briefly explain what a transaction is along with the ACID properties.
Ans:To maintain the integrity of the data,there are four properties described in dbms,which are known as the ACID properties.
the full form of ACID is
--Atomicity:
          data remains single or atomic.if any operation performed on the data,either it should be performed or should not performed at all.

--Consistency:
             The databases remains n a consistent state after any transaction;
--Isolation:
            A transaction can not effect another transaction ,it is isololated;
--Durabilty:
            History of a  transaction must be preserved;